B017 [1362-1364]: In late July 2016, the Company received six LOIs with offer prices per share ranging from $19.20 to $24.00 (implying equity values of $96 million to $121 million). Party B, G& W and another bidder ( Party D) also provided mark-ups of the draft merger agreement and voting agreement. One bidder ( Party E) provided a summary of material issues and proposed changes to the merger agreement and voting agreement with respect to those issues.

